The paper deals with the problem of network slicing and power allocation in a wireless communication system, which is a topic that falls under the domain of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also involves optimization techniques and algorithms for solving the problem, which is a common theme in information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of cloud computing and virtual network functions also suggests a possible fit with distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper deals with the design and implementation of a flexible and open radio access network, which could be relevant to the field of computer architecture and embedded systems (cs.AR).
